# RetailerBoost Landing Page - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

This is a static HTML landing page for RetailerBoost outbound marketing campaigns. The site is deployed via GitHub Pages and consists of static HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript.

## Language & Spelling

- **Use USA English spellings** (e.g., "color" not "colour", "center" not "centre", "organization" not "organisation")
- Common examples:
  - favor, favorite (not favour, favourite)
  - analyze (not analyse)
  - customize (not customise)
  - optimize (not optimise)
  - fulfill (not fulfil)
  - canceled (not cancelled)

## Code Style

### HTML

- Use semantic HTML5 elements where appropriate
- Keep inline styles to a minimum - prefer CSS classes
- Use double quotes for attributes
- Include alt text on all images
- Use proper indentation (2 spaces)
- Add HTML comments to mark major sections: `<!-- Section Name -->`

### CSS

- Use the existing color scheme:
  - Primary Blue: `#247CFF`
  - Secondary Blue: `#1A64CC`
  - Teal (checkmarks/accents): `#33D0C4`
  - Background: `#0B1314`
  - Text Primary: `#fff`
  - Text Secondary: `#e5e5e5`
  - Text Muted: `#aaa`
- Prefer CSS classes over inline styles for reusable components
- Use existing CSS classes from `_next/static/css/` files where available
- Mobile-first responsive design with breakpoints at 768px and 880px

### JavaScript

- Use vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Use `'use strict';` in all scripts
- Prefer `var` for broader browser compatibility in inline scripts
- Use descriptive function and variable names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep scripts at the bottom of the body or use DOMContentLoaded

## Content Guidelines

### Emojis

- **Limit emoji usage** - only use where they add clear value
- Acceptable uses: Section headers with icons (e.g., scenarios cards), testimonial hearts
- Avoid: Body text, CTAs, navigation
- Never use multiple emojis in sequence

### Copy Style

- Keep sentences concise and scannable
- Use active voice
- Focus on benefits, not features
- Avoid jargon - write for merchants, not marketers
- No em dashes (use hyphens or rewrite)

## URLs & Links

### Get Started CTAs

All "Get Started" buttons should link to:
```
https://dashboard.retailerboost.com/signup?utm_source=...&utm_medium=...&utm_campaign=...&utm_content=...
```

UTM parameters are dynamically updated by the UTM passthrough script. Default values:
- `utm_source`: retailerboostplatform.com
- `utm_medium`: outbound
- `utm_campaign`: email
- `utm_content`: [location identifier]

### Book a Call CTAs

Use Calendly popup:
```javascript
Calendly.initPopupWidget({url: 'https://calendly.com/sturrock/intro?hide_event_type_details=1&hide_gdpr_banner=1&primary_color=247CFF'});return false;
```

## Component Patterns

### FAQ Item
```html
<div class="faq-item">
  <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open');">
    <h4>Question text here?</h4>
    <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
  </button>
  <div class="faq-answer">
    <p>Answer text here.</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Card Component
```html
<div style="background:rgba(36,124,255,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(36,124,255,0.2);border-radius:16px;padding:2rem;">
  <h3 style="color:#247CFF;">Title</h3>
  <p style="color:#e5e5e5;">Description</p>
</div>
```

### Primary CTA Button
```html
<a href="..." style="display:inline-block;padding:1rem 2.5rem;background:linear-gradient(135deg, #247CFF, #1A64CC);color:#fff;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;border-radius:8px;">
  Button Text
</a>
```

### Secondary/Ghost CTA Button
```html
<a href="..." style="display:inline-block;padding:1rem 2.5rem;background:transparent;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;border-radius:8px;border:2px solid #247CFF;">
  Button Text
</a>
```

